  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">National Initiatives for Sustainable &amp; Climate Smart oil Palm Smallholders Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Ghana, a total of 1,087 smallholder farmers received training in climate smart agriculture while 928 artisanal processors were trained in Health and Safety. Four of our partner districts distributed 187,000 improved seedlings translating to about 1,300 hectares, which is significant to replace farms destroyed by illegal small-scale mining. Additionally, efforts were made to link farmers to farm services companies, through networking events and the dissemination of IVR messages to 4,796 NI-SCOPS beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
